data.title: How to watch: TV, radio info for Cardinals at Vikings game
data.meta_description: The Cardinals have not won a game at Minnesota since\u00a01977.
data.text:
Following their first win of the season, the Arizona Cardinals prepare for Sunday's game against the Minnesota Vikings.

The Cardinals defense forced five takeaways at San Francisco last week. Vikings' quarterback Kirk Cousins has thrown 11 touchdowns and just two interceptions through five weeks.

The Cardinals have not won a game at Minnesota since 1977.

Sunday's game

Arizona Cardinals (1-4) at Minnesota Vikings (2-2-1)

When: 10 a.m.

TV: Channel 10. Play-by-play: Sam Rosen. Analyst: Ronde Barber. Sideline: Shane Bacon.

Radio: KMVP-FM 98.7. Play-by-play: Dave Pasch. Analyst: Ron Wolfley. Sideline: Paul Calvisi.

Spanish radio: KHOV-FM 105.1. Play-by-play: Gabriel Trujillo. Analyst: Rolando Cantu.
